    • Constructor Detail

      • GameObj

        public GameObj(int gameId,
               List<ToClientPacket> txQueue,
               PlayerObj p1,
               PlayerObj p2)
        The gameobject connects the players to the game objects via methods. It also handles error messages and is able to send network messages. If no player has configured settings defaults are taken. The board is initialized. A gui is initialized.
        Parameters:
        clientId - The clientId of the target
        skt - socket object "socket.accept()'ed"

        public void doMoveForPlayer(int clientId,
                            int row,
                            int col)
        The move is executed if it is valid. In order to establish the validity of the move the board object (final) associated to the game is used to cather out the move.
        Parameters:
        clientId - The clientId of the target
        row - row of the move position
        col - collumn of the move position
